# Phase 2 — Buffered Recording, IStreamTransmitter,> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Buffer Exhaustion Resolution**: The `RequestWrap` assertion in `libcamerasrc` typically occurs when the buffer pool is exhausted. Since we must keep the **1080p source resolution**, we will compensate by increasing `libcamerasrc buffer-count=12` (allowing more frames to be in-flight) and adding decoupling `queue` elements.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Pipeline Decoupling**: We will insert GStreamer `queue` elements between the source and conversion stages to ensure the camera hardware isn't blocked by transient processing spikes in the AI or UI threads.

